<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Martin_Seligman" title="Martin Seligman">Seligman, Martin E.P.</a> (2002). <i>Authentic Happiness: Using the New Positive Psychology to Realize Your Potential for Lasting Fulfillment</i>. New York: Simon and Schuster. p. xi. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0743222970" class="internal">ISBN 0-7432-2297-0</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> "The science of psychology has been far more successful on the negative than on the positive side. It has revealed to us much about man’s shortcomings, his illness, his sins, but little about his potentialities, his virtues, his achievable aspirations, or his full psychological height. It is as if psychology has voluntarily restricted itself to only half its rightful jurisdiction, than the darker, meaner half." (Maslow, Motivation and Psychology, p. 354).</li>
<li id="cite_note-Seligman2002-8">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Seligman2002_8-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSeligman2009">Seligman, Martin E.P. (2002). <i>Authentic Happiness: Using the New Positive Psychology to Realize Your Potential for Lasting Fulfillment.</i>. New York: Simon and Schuster. pp.&#160;275. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0743222970" class="internal">ISBN 0-7432-2297-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Authentic+Happiness%3A+Using+the+New+Positive+Psychology+to+Realize+Your+Potential+for+Lasting+Fulfillment.&amp;rft.aulast=Seligman&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin+E.P.&amp;rft.au=Seligman%2C+Martin+E.P.&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B275&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Simon+and+Schuster&amp;rft.isbn=0-7432-2297-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Positive_psychology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.unc.edu/peplab/publications/undo_2000.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.unc.edu/peplab/publications/undo_2000.pdf" rel="nofollow">Fredrickson, B. L., Mancuso, R. A., Branigan, C., &amp; Tugade, M. M. (2000). "The undoing effect of positive emotions," <i>Motivation and Emotion</i>. 24, 237-258.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.thestar.com/living/article/551538" class="external text" title="http://www.thestar.com/living/article/551538" rel="nofollow">"New emotion dubbed 'elevation"</a> (in English). <a href="/wiki/Toronto_Star" title="Toronto Star">Toronto Star</a>. December 11, 2008<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.thestar.com/living/article/551538" class="external free" title="http://www.thestar.com/living/article/551538" rel="nofollow">http://www.thestar.com/living/article/551538</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=New+emotion+dubbed+%27elevation&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=December+11%2C+2008&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BToronto+Star%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestar.com%2Fliving%2Farticle%2F551538&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Positive_psychology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-IPP2-11">^ <a href="#cite_ref-IPP2_11-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-IPP2_11-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCompton2009">Compton, William C, (2005). "2". <i>An Introduction to Positive Psychology</i>. <a href="/wiki/Wadsworth_Publishing" title="Wadsworth Publishing" class="mw-redirect">Wadsworth Publishing</a>. pp.&#160;23–40. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0534644538" class="internal">ISBN 0-534-64453-8</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=2&amp;rft.atitle=An+Introduction+to+Positive+Psychology&amp;rft.aulast=Compton&amp;rft.aufirst=William+C%2C&amp;rft.au=Compton%2C+William+C%2C&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B23%E2%80%9340&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BWadsworth+Publishing%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-534-64453-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Positive_psychology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
